WEBVTT

00:06.200 --> 00:11.160
Captions made possible by
HOME BOX OFFICE, INC.

01:50.910 --> 01:52.207
COME ON, I'M OPEN,
OVER HERE !

01:52.310 --> 01:54.471
OH MY GOD,
PASS THE BALL !

01:54.580 --> 01:57.208
C'MON !

01:57.310 --> 01:59.210
MY GRANDMA CAN KICK
HARDER THAN THAT !

02:04.950 --> 02:06.042
GOT IT !

02:06.160 --> 02:09.323
COME HERE BABY,
LET'S GET YOU FIXED UP.

02:09.430 --> 02:10.089
SHOO !

02:10.190 --> 02:11.680
GO ON, NOW.

02:11.790 --> 02:16.056
RODERICK, CAN I OFFER YOU
A SLICE OF MY BU'I'I'ERMILK PIE ?

02:16.170 --> 02:18.126
IS THAT THE SAME PIE
YOU MADE LAST YEAR ?

02:18.230 --> 02:19.868
YES, IT IS.

02:19.970 --> 02:20.937
THEN, UH...

02:21.040 --> 02:22.268
NO, THANK YOU.

02:22.370 --> 02:24.235
RODERICK,
CAN'T YOU BE NICE ?

02:24.340 --> 02:25.659
SHE'S YOUR AUNT.

02:25.770 --> 02:27.237
YOU EAT HER
SOUR PIE.

02:27.340 --> 02:31.276
WELL, MAYBE I'LL HAVE
ONE MORE SMALL PIECE.

02:31.380 --> 02:33.848
I'LL HAVE
A PIECE OF PIE.

02:35.280 --> 02:37.419
OW, DAMMIT.

02:37.520 --> 02:40.114
AUNT JEANIE,
DID YOU GET STUNG ?

02:40.220 --> 02:41.255
WHY YES.

02:41.360 --> 02:43.749
I GOT STUNG BY
A BEE BEFORE.

02:43.860 --> 02:45.179
IT'S NOT THAT BAD.

02:45.290 --> 02:46.826
SHE'S ALLERGIC,
I'M CALLING 911.

02:46.930 --> 02:49.592
( breathing heavily)

02:49.700 --> 02:51.258
HELLO ?

02:51.370 --> 02:52.462
( Taylor )
AUNT JEANIE ?

02:52.570 --> 02:54.037
I'M CALLING FROM
BALBOA PARK.

02:54.140 --> 02:55.266
MY WIFE'S AUNT
GOT STUNG BY A BEE.

02:55.370 --> 02:56.735
SHE'S HAVING AN
ALLERGIC REACTION.

02:56.840 --> 02:57.738
AUNT JEANIE !

02:57.840 --> 02:59.501
AUNT JEANIE !

02:59.610 --> 03:00.429
TALK TO THEM !

03:00.540 --> 03:01.871
HELLO ?

03:01.980 --> 03:04.972
BY THE EAST ENTRANCE, WHERE YOU
WALK DOWN THE LITTLE HILL.

03:05.080 --> 03:08.243
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH HER ?

03:08.350 --> 03:10.045
IS SHE GONNA BE OKAY ?

03:10.150 --> 03:11.879
SHE'S GONNA BE OKAY,
SWEETHEART.

03:11.990 --> 03:13.480
HELP'S ON THE WAY.

03:13.590 --> 03:15.751
JEANIE ?

03:15.860 --> 03:17.487
AUNT JEANIE ?

03:25.570 --> 03:27.037
BABY, THAT FEELS
SO GOOD.

03:27.140 --> 03:29.301
( moaning )

03:36.750 --> 03:39.378
OH MY GOD, WOW !

03:39.480 --> 03:41.539
THAT WAS NICE, BABY.

03:41.650 --> 03:43.140
NICE ?

03:43.250 --> 03:44.945
THAT WAS AMAZING.

03:45.050 --> 03:47.757
IT'S GREAT THAT,

03:47.860 --> 03:50.988
YOU KNOW,
YOU WANTED TO.

03:52.230 --> 03:54.653
OF COURSE
I WANTED TO.

03:54.760 --> 04:00.835
I MEAN, IT'S BEEN
A LONG TIME SINCE YOU...

04:02.100 --> 04:05.228
I MEAN, IT'S GREAT
THAT YOU WANTED TO.

04:10.350 --> 04:13.046
I HAVE A SURPRISE
FOR YOU.

04:13.150 --> 04:17.280
WHOA, OKAY.

04:17.390 --> 04:20.086
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
TO GIVE ME FIVE MINUTES THOUGH.

04:20.190 --> 04:21.487
10 MINUTES, TOPS.

04:21.590 --> 04:24.229
NO, IT'S A DIFFERENT
KIND OF SURPRISE.

04:24.330 --> 04:27.629
I SIGNED US UP FOR
A DANCE CLASS TONIGHT.

04:32.500 --> 04:35.537
A DANCE CLASS,
REALLY ?

04:35.640 --> 04:38.108
SALSA, TANGO, MERENGUE.

04:38.210 --> 04:39.837
OH, MERENGUE.

04:39.940 --> 04:44.377
WOW, MY MOM
USED TO DO THAT.

04:44.480 --> 04:46.778
SHE WON TROPHIES.

04:46.880 --> 04:49.019
MAYBE I'LL WIN ONE.

04:49.120 --> 04:51.816
I'M GONNA GO
MAKE SOME COFFEE.

04:51.920 --> 04:54.718
NO, NO,
I'LL DO IT !

04:57.060 --> 05:00.996
JULIO, AUGUSTO,
TIME TO GET UP !

05:01.100 --> 05:03.796
BY DIPPING THE SPONGE APPLICATOR
IN THE COLD WATER

05:03.900 --> 05:07.131
AND APPLYING IT TO BARBIE'S
LIPS, CHEEKS, AND EYELIDS

05:07.240 --> 05:09.538
YOU GET FLOURISH
OF GLAMOROUS COLOR.

05:09.640 --> 05:11.403
I'M TELLING TAYLOR
YOU TOOK IT OUT OF THE BOX.

05:11.510 --> 05:14.707
WHEN I WAS A KID,
I USED TO HAVE G-I JOES.

05:14.810 --> 05:18.439
THEY WERE ALWAYS GETTING
COURT-MARSHALED,

05:18.550 --> 05:21.542
WHICH, IN MY VERSION,
MEANT THEY HAD TO STAND NAKED

05:21.650 --> 05:22.947
IN FRONT OF ALL
THE OTHER DOLLS.

05:23.050 --> 05:26.588
50, IS THAT SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO ACT OUT ?

05:26.690 --> 05:30.126
I THINK WE'VE HAD ENOUGH
EXCITEMENT FOR A WHILE.

05:30.230 --> 05:32.994
THE THREE-WAYS ?

05:33.100 --> 05:34.158
WELL, YEAH.

05:34.260 --> 05:36.626
WHAT ABOUT THEM ?

05:36.730 --> 05:38.425
DON'T YOU THINK
THAT MAYBE

05:38.530 --> 05:40.191
THEY'RE NOT THE BEST
THING FOR US ?

05:40.300 --> 05:41.631
OH, REALLY ?

05:41.740 --> 05:43.367
SO, THAT WASN'T YOU
THE OTHER NIGHT

05:43.470 --> 05:46.030
THAT KEPT BEGGING US TO ARREST
AND INTERROGATE YOU ?

05:46.140 --> 05:47.277
I'M NOT SAYING
THEY'RE NOT FUN.

05:47.380 --> 05:49.678
SO, WHAT ARE
YOU SAYING ?

05:49.780 --> 05:51.907
I'M JUST STARTING
TO FEEL WEIRD ABOUT IT.

05:52.010 --> 05:54.615
OKAY, FINE.

05:54.720 --> 05:56.449
FINE ?

05:56.550 --> 05:58.086
YEAH, WHATEVER.

05:58.190 --> 05:59.418
KEITH, THAT IS
SO NOT FAIR.

05:59.520 --> 06:00.885
YOU ASK ME TO TELL YOU
HOW I FEEL ABOUT SOMETHING

06:00.990 --> 06:02.582
AND THEN WHEN I DO,
YOU JUST SHUT DOWN.

06:02.690 --> 06:04.658
I JUST DON'T FEEL LIKE
TALKING ABOUT IT RIGHT NOW.

06:04.760 --> 06:07.593
YOU'RE JUST ALL TENSE BECAUSE
WE'RE GOING TO SEE YOUR FATHER.

06:07.700 --> 06:09.895
WEE GOING TO
MY GREAT AUNT'S FUNERAL.

06:10.000 --> 06:11.592
WHERE YOUR FATHER
WILL BE

06:11.700 --> 06:13.634
AND WHOSE HOUSE
WE'LL BE STAYING AT.

06:13.740 --> 06:15.765
SO, I DON'T HAVE
A PROBLEM WITH HIM.

06:15.870 --> 06:17.531
OH, REALLY ?

06:17.640 --> 06:20.200
YEAH, I'VE BEEN WORKING ON
ALL THAT STUFF

06:20.310 --> 06:21.777
IN MY INDIVIDUAL THERAPY.

06:21.880 --> 06:23.575
REALLY ?

06:23.680 --> 06:25.443
THAT'S ALL
I TALK ABOUT.

06:25.550 --> 06:27.814
HOW COME YOU'VE NEVER
TOLD ME ANY OF THIS ?

06:27.920 --> 06:31.310
BECAUSE SOME THINGS ARE JUST
BETWEEN ME AND THE THERAPIST.

06:31.420 --> 06:34.116
I TELL YOU EVERYTHING.

06:34.220 --> 06:36.154
THAT'S BECAUSE
YOU NT MY APPROVAL.

06:36.260 --> 06:39.559
NO, IT'S BECAUSE
I LOVE YOU.

06:41.930 --> 06:43.989
AND THE OTHER GENTLEMAN,
HE'S YOUR BROTHER ?

06:44.100 --> 06:45.897
YES, DAVID.

06:46.000 --> 06:47.467
THAT'S WHO HELPED ME.

06:47.570 --> 06:50.300
HE LEFI' THIS MORNING
FOR A FRIEND'S FUNERAL.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.105
HE SOLD ME A CASKET.

06:52.210 --> 06:55.577
YES, THE CAMEO ROSE.

06:55.680 --> 06:57.102
IT'S NOT
GOOD ENOUGH.

06:57.210 --> 07:01.442
MR. FASTEAU, THE CAMEO ROSE
IS AN EXCELLENT CASKET.

07:01.550 --> 07:03.882
NO, I WANT SOMETHING
NICER FOR MARTHA.

07:03.990 --> 07:06.686
AND IT DOESN'T MATTER
HOW MUCH IT COSTS.

07:06.790 --> 07:09.623
I KNOW THAT WHEN
WE LOSE SOMEONE

07:09.730 --> 07:12.551
WE WANT TO SHOW
HOW MUCH WE LOVED HER,

07:12.660 --> 07:15.049
AND WE'RE AT A LOSS
AS TO HOW TO DO THAT,

07:15.160 --> 07:17.720
AND WE END UP SPENDING A LOT
OF MONEY ON SOMETHING THAT,

07:17.830 --> 07:19.832
IN THE END,
ISN'T REALLY NECESSARY.

07:19.940 --> 07:20.964
I DON'T CARE !

07:21.070 --> 07:22.628
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND,

07:22.740 --> 07:27.109
THIS IS THE LAST THING I'LL EVER
BE ABLE TO DO FOR MY WIFE ?

07:27.210 --> 07:32.000
THAT I WAS
A BAD HUSBAND.

07:32.110 --> 07:35.546
AFFAIRS AND
ALL THAT SHIT.

07:35.650 --> 07:41.008
THEN I GOT CANCER,
THOUGHT I WAS GOING TO DIE.

07:41.120 --> 07:43.384
BUT I GOT BETTER.

07:43.490 --> 07:45.651
I GOT A SECOND CHANCE.

07:45.760 --> 07:48.957
AND I REALIZED
HOW MUCH I LOVED HER.

07:49.060 --> 07:52.359
AND IT'S BEEN REALLY GOOD
THE LAST FEW YEARS.

07:52.470 --> 07:58.705
I JUST WANT
TO LOVE HER SOME MORE.

07:58.810 --> 08:01.870
I OWE HER.

08:01.980 --> 08:04.574
OH GOD...

08:04.680 --> 08:07.945
OH GOD, I LOVED HER,
I REALLY DID.

08:08.050 --> 08:10.018
OF COURSE YOU DID,
OF COURSE YOU DID.

08:10.120 --> 08:11.018
AND SHE KNEW THAT.

08:12.190 --> 08:13.919
SHE...

08:14.020 --> 08:18.127
WAS EVERYTHING TO ME.

08:23.330 --> 08:25.195
I AM SO SORRY.

08:37.180 --> 08:41.276
NATE, DO YOU REMEMBER
WHEN I USED TO MAKE

08:41.380 --> 08:42.984
THAT CASSEROLE
WITH THE...

08:43.090 --> 08:46.082
(crying )

08:58.470 --> 09:00.688
I USED TO DO THIS
FOR YOUR FATHER.

09:00.800 --> 09:03.837
HIS SHOULDERS WOULD GET
SO FULL OF KNOTS.

09:03.940 --> 09:08.309
IT'S SUCH
A STRESSFUL JOB.

09:20.290 --> 09:22.417
IT'S OKAY, BABY.

09:22.520 --> 09:24.681
IT'S OKAY.

09:41.910 --> 09:44.140
HEY, DO YOU WANT
THE FRONT PAGE ?

09:44.250 --> 09:47.344
NO, I CAN'T DEAL WITH
DEPRESSING NEWS RIGHT NOW.

09:50.650 --> 09:52.789
GOD, I DON'T REMEMBER
THIS BOOK BEING SO DARK.

09:52.890 --> 09:55.415
THESE KIDS IN THE ORPHANAGE
ARE BEING TORTURED.

09:55.520 --> 09:57.488
OH, THAT'S
THE BEST PART.

09:57.590 --> 09:59.353
WHERE THEY ALL HAVE
TO TAKE A BATH IN ICE WATER.

09:59.460 --> 10:01.553
WELL, YEAH.

10:01.660 --> 10:03.366
ISN'T THAT KIND OF
INAPPROPRIATE FOR KIDS ?

10:03.470 --> 10:05.028
COME ON,
WE'RE HUMAN BEINGS.

10:05.130 --> 10:08.258
WE ALL HAVE A SICK CRAVING
FOR THAT KIND OF DARK FANTASY.

10:08.370 --> 10:09.735
EVEN KIDS.

10:09.840 --> 10:11.603
I'VE HAD ENOUGH
DARK REALITY.

10:11.710 --> 10:13.075
I DON'T NEED
THE FANTASY.

10:15.010 --> 10:16.375
OH, JESUS.

10:16.480 --> 10:17.674
HMM ?

10:17.780 --> 10:21.318
NURSE CATERWAUL IS MAKING
NATHANIEL AND ISABEL

10:21.420 --> 10:23.012
CANE EACH OTHER.

10:23.120 --> 10:24.439
OH, READ THAT
PART OUT LOUD !

10:24.550 --> 10:25.983
YOU'RE SICK.

10:26.090 --> 10:28.888
IF BY THAT YOU MEAN SUFFERING
FROM BIPOLAR DISORDER

10:28.990 --> 10:31.424
WITH OCCASIONAL
PSYCHOTIC EPISODES,
THEN YES, I AM.

10:31.530 --> 10:33.896
HMM, HMM...

10:38.800 --> 10:41.291
THIS IS GOOD,
CLAIRE.

10:41.400 --> 10:42.662
IT'S LOVELY.

10:42.770 --> 10:46.206
THE BLURRINESS, THE WAY
THE LIGHT SEEMS TOO MUCH,

10:46.310 --> 10:49.199
AS IF THERE'S A SECRET FIRE
IN HER THAT'S SPILLING OUT

10:49.310 --> 10:51.540
FOR JUST A MOMENT AND YOU
WERE THERE TO CAPTURE IT.

10:51.650 --> 10:55.074
EXCELLENT WORK !

10:55.180 --> 10:56.738
THAN KS.

11:00.320 --> 11:02.584
IT ONLY TURNED OUT
THIS WAY

11:02.690 --> 11:04.385
BECAUSE I ACCIDENTALLY
DRAGGED THE SHUTTER.

11:04.490 --> 11:06.424
I WAS TOTALLY GONNA
RESHOOT IT.

11:06.530 --> 11:09.124
BUT HE'S RIGHT,
IT WORKS.

11:09.230 --> 11:11.528
IT'S REALLY GOOD.

11:11.630 --> 11:14.929
I WONDER HOW MUCH OF ART
REALLY IS ACCIDENTAL.

11:15.040 --> 11:16.905
I MEAN,
MAYBE LIKE MAGRITTE

11:17.010 --> 11:19.069
WHEN HE WAS PAINTING
HIS LISTENING ROOM

11:19.170 --> 11:21.434
WAS LIKE, "DAMN, I MADE
THE APPLE TOO BIG AGAIN."

11:21.540 --> 11:25.340
HELLO, I'M BEING
CLEVER OVER HERE ?

11:25.450 --> 11:27.213
SHIT !

11:27.320 --> 11:28.344
WHAT ?

11:28.450 --> 11:31.010
THE BLADE'S DULL.

11:31.120 --> 11:32.542
IT'S FUCKING UP
EVERYTHING.

11:32.650 --> 11:34.686
USE ANOTHER ONE.

11:34.790 --> 11:37.054
I'VE GOT 10 MATTES TO CUT,
I DON'T HAVE TIME.

11:37.160 --> 11:39.890
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU JUST
CHANGE THE BLADE, HERE ?

11:40.000 --> 11:40.989
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT
TO JUST CHANGE THE BLADE.

11:41.100 --> 11:42.761
BECAUSE IT'S
ALL JUST SHIT.

11:42.870 --> 11:44.667
I HATE IT,
I HATE EVERYTHING !

11:44.770 --> 11:46.397
I HATE THIS
PIECE OF SHIT !

11:46.500 --> 11:48.229
IT'S ALL
FUCKING SHIT !

11:48.340 --> 11:50.865
GOOD, A TANTRUM.

11:50.970 --> 11:53.438
THIS IS AN OPPORTUNITY
TO LEARN, PEOPLE.

11:53.540 --> 11:56.373
RUSSELL,
YOU HATE YOUR WORK,

11:56.480 --> 11:58.038
BECAUSE YOU SECRETLY
HATE YOURSELF.

11:58.150 --> 12:00.539
WHICH MEANS THAT YOU'RE
STILL ONLY THINKING ABOUT

12:00.650 --> 12:01.776
AND LOOKING
AT YOURSELF.

12:01.880 --> 12:03.211
YEAH, WHATEVER.

12:03.320 --> 12:05.288
YEAH, WHATEVER,
BUT I UNDERSTAND THE IMPULSE.

12:05.390 --> 12:08.712
I ONCE FILLED THE TRUNK OF
MY CAR WITH ALL MY LATEST WORK

12:08.820 --> 12:10.685
AND THEN LIT
THE CAR ON FIRE

12:10.790 --> 12:13.554
AND LET IT ROLL DOWN
THE STREETS OF MONMARTE.

12:13.660 --> 12:15.855
WOW, THAT'S INTERESTING.

12:15.960 --> 12:19.066
BECAUSE EVERYTHING YOU DO IS
JUST SO FUCKING FASCINATING.

12:19.170 --> 12:21.991
OOH, SUCH VITRIOL
AND SUCH RAGE.

12:22.100 --> 12:24.568
AND WHY AREN'T YOU PUTTING
THIS INTO YOUR WORK ?

12:24.670 --> 12:27.036
WELL, YOU TELL ME
SOMETHING, OLIVIER.

12:27.140 --> 12:28.732
IF YOU KNOW SO MUCH
ABOUT ART AND LIFE,

12:28.840 --> 12:31.377
HOW COME YOU ENDED UP
BEING SUCH A PATHETIC POSER

12:31.480 --> 12:33.914
WHO NEEDS PEOPLE
HALF HIS AGE TO PROP HIM UP

12:34.020 --> 12:37.080
AND MAKE HIM FEEL GOOD
ABOUT HIMSELF ?

12:42.990 --> 12:46.187
HE COULD HAVE AT LEAST MADE
THE EFFORT TO SLAM THE DOOR.

12:46.290 --> 12:50.499
YOUNG PEOPLE HAVE ABSOLUTELY
NO COMMITMENT TODAY.

12:50.600 --> 12:54.366
GO BACK TO WORK !

13:01.510 --> 13:03.603
HEY, YOU OKAY ?

13:03.710 --> 13:06.474
YEAH, SORRY
ABOUT THAT.

13:06.580 --> 13:09.014
JUST A LITTLE
MELTDOWN.

13:09.120 --> 13:10.485
YEAH.

13:10.590 --> 13:12.410
I CAN STAY,
GO ANOTHER TIME.

13:12.520 --> 13:13.987
NO, NO, NO,
YOU'RE GOING.

13:14.090 --> 13:16.854
YOU NEED A BREAK,
YOU DESERVE A BREAK.

13:16.960 --> 13:18.484
YOU WANT
TO GET RID OF ME.

13:18.590 --> 13:19.727
NO, OF COURSE NOT.

13:19.830 --> 13:21.991
BUT IT'S FIVE HOURS
TO SANTA CRUZ

13:22.100 --> 13:23.567
AND YOU WANT TO GET TO YOUR
SISTER'S BEFORE DARK, RIGHT ?

13:23.670 --> 13:27.367
I FEEL LIKE SUCH A TERRIBLE
MOTHER FOR THINKING THIS,

13:27.470 --> 13:29.597
AND I KNOW AS SOON AS I WALK OUT
THE DOOR I'M GONNA MISS HER,

13:29.700 --> 13:32.828
BUT I'M KINDA LOOKING FORWARD
TO A COUPLE DAYS WITHOUT MAYA.

13:32.940 --> 13:37.877
THAT'S BECAUSE YOU'RE
A HANDFUL, AREN'T YOU ?

13:37.980 --> 13:40.312
SO, DID YOU MAKE
A LIST FOR ME ?

13:40.420 --> 13:41.717
A LIST FOR WHAT ?

13:41.820 --> 13:43.185
I DON'T KNOW,
USUALLY YOU MAKE LISTS.

13:43.290 --> 13:45.941
WHAT TIME I'M SUPPOSED
TO FEED MAYA,

13:46.050 --> 13:47.756
WHAT I CAN FEED HER,
WHAT I CAN'T FEED HER.

13:47.860 --> 13:49.714
YOU ALREADY KNOW
ALL THAT STUFF.

13:49.820 --> 13:51.583
YEAH, OKAY.

13:51.690 --> 13:53.829
JUST DON'T LET YOUR
MOTHER BATHE HER.

13:53.930 --> 13:55.158
IT'S LIKE SHE'S
SCRUBBING A POTATO.

13:55.260 --> 13:57.967
ALRIGHT,
I'LL BATHE HER.

13:58.530 --> 14:00.361
OKAY.

14:04.440 --> 14:06.135
I'M GONNA MISS YOU.

14:06.240 --> 14:09.209
MM-WAH !

14:09.310 --> 14:11.574
C'MON, WE'LL WALK YOU
TO THE CAR.

14:11.680 --> 14:13.272
NO, I DON'T WANT MAYA
TO SEE ME GO.

14:13.380 --> 14:14.608
I JUST DON'T.

14:14.720 --> 14:17.245
WELL.

14:17.350 --> 14:18.214
I LOVE YOU.

14:18.320 --> 14:18.979
GOODBYE THEN.

14:19.090 --> 14:21.809
BE GOOD TO DADDY,
RIGHT ?

14:21.920 --> 14:23.478
I LOVE YOU.

14:23.590 --> 14:25.558
BYE.

14:38.610 --> 14:40.407
ARTHUR,
ARE YOU BUSY ?

14:40.510 --> 14:42.239
I'M PUTTING AWAY
MY SOCKS.

14:42.340 --> 14:47.972
BUT I'VE BECOME CONFUSED AS
TO WHICH IS PAIRED WITH WHICH.

14:48.080 --> 14:51.481
THEY ALL LOOK
EXACTLY THE SAME.

14:51.590 --> 14:53.683
THUS, THE DILEMMA.

14:53.790 --> 14:56.315
ARTHUR, I REALLY
NEED TO TALK.

14:56.420 --> 14:58.957
OKAY.

15:03.730 --> 15:05.027
QUITE FRAN KLY,

15:05.130 --> 15:07.633
I'D LIKE TO KNOW
HOW YOU FEEL ABOUT

15:07.740 --> 15:09.367
THE COURSE OUR
RELATIONSHIP IS TAKING.

15:09.470 --> 15:10.698
AH.

15:10.810 --> 15:13.233
WE'VE BEEN ON QUITE
A SERENDIPITOUS JOURNEY,
HAVEN'T WE ?

15:13.340 --> 15:16.798
AND WHERE DO YOU
THINK IT'S HEADED ?

15:16.910 --> 15:18.639
SURELY SOMEPLACE DIVINE.

15:18.750 --> 15:21.116
DOES THAT MEAN...

15:21.220 --> 15:23.814
WELL, YOU KNOW,
INTIMACY ?

15:23.920 --> 15:26.616
I LOVE INTIMACY,
INTIMACY IS MY BEST FRIEND.

15:26.720 --> 15:29.689
ARTHUR,
I'M SO CONFUSED.

15:29.790 --> 15:32.657
DO YOU FIND ME
AT ALL ATTRACTIVE ?

15:32.760 --> 15:34.398
IF YOU FEEL I'M
TOO OLD FOR YOU--

15:34.500 --> 15:35.728
HEAVENS NO !

15:35.830 --> 15:38.594
YOU'RE THE PERFECT AGE
FOR ME, RUTH FISHER.

15:38.700 --> 15:39.792
IAM?

15:39.900 --> 15:41.333
ABSOLUTELY.

15:41.440 --> 15:43.567
SO HOW DO YOU FEEL ABOUT US
HAVING, YOU KNOW, SEX ?

15:43.670 --> 15:45.638
OH.

15:45.740 --> 15:48.106
OH MY.

15:48.210 --> 15:49.802
IT'S JUST THAT WE'VE BEEN SEEING
EACH OTHER FOR A WHILE AND...

15:49.910 --> 15:52.003
NOT EVEN A KISS.

15:52.110 --> 15:54.112
WELL, NOT SINCE--

15:54.220 --> 15:56.108
YES, I UNDERSTAND.

